      "source": [
        "# Install if needed\n",
        "!pip install graphviz --quiet\n",
        "\n",
        "# Import libraries\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from sklearn.datasets import load_breast_cancer\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, cross_val_score\n",
        "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier, export_graphviz\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n",
        "import graphviz\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load data\n",
        "data = load_breast_cancer()\n",
        "X = pd.DataFrame(data.data, columns=data.feature_names)\n",
        "y = pd.Series(data.target)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Split data\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1 Decision Tree & visualize\n",
        "tree = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=5, random_state=42)\n",
        "tree.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "dot_data = export_graphviz(tree, out_file=None,\n",
        "                           feature_names=data.feature_names,\n",
        "                           class_names=data.target_names,\n",
        "                           filled=True, rounded=True)\n",
        "graph = graphviz.Source(dot_data)\n",
        "graph.render(\"decision_tree_breast_cancer\")\n",
        "print(\"Decision tree saved as decision_tree_breast_cancer.pdf\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2 Analyze overfitting by depth\n",
        "depths = [3, 5, 10, None]\n",
        "train_acc_list = []\n",
        "test_acc_list = []\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nDepth analysis:\")\n",
        "for depth in depths:\n",
        "    model = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=depth, random_state=42)\n",
        "    model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "    train_acc = accuracy_score(y_train, model.predict(X_train))\n",
        "    test_acc = accuracy_score(y_test, model.predict(X_test))\n",
        "    train_acc_list.append(train_acc)\n",
        "    test_acc_list.append(test_acc)\n",
        "    print(f\"Max depth={depth}: Train acc={train_acc:.2f}, Test acc={test_acc:.2f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot depth vs accuracy\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))\n",
        "plt.plot([str(d) for d in depths], train_acc_list, marker='o', label='Train Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.plot([str(d) for d in depths], test_acc_list, marker='o', label='Test Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Max Depth')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.title('Decision Tree Depth vs Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3 Random Forest\n",
        "forest = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, max_depth=5, random_state=42)\n",
        "forest.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "y_pred_tree = tree.predict(X_test)\n",
        "y_pred_forest = forest.predict(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nDecision Tree Test Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_tree):.2f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Random Forest Test Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_forest):.2f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4 Feature importances\n",
        "importances = pd.Series(forest.feature_importances_, index=data.feature_names)\n",
        "importances_sorted = importances.sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nTop 5 important features (Random Forest):\")\n",
        "print(importances_sorted.head())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot feature importances\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))\n",
        "importances_sorted.head(10).plot(kind='barh')\n",
        "plt.title('Top 10 Feature Importances (Random Forest)')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Importance')\n",
        "plt.gca().invert_yaxis()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5 Cross-validation\n",
        "cv_scores = cross_val_score(forest, X, y, cv=5)\n",
        "print(f\"\\nRandom Forest 5-fold CV Accuracy: {cv_scores.mean():.2f} (+/- {cv_scores.std():.2f})\")"
      ]
    }
